\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
\int_{0}^{T}f(x)dx & = & F(T)-F(0)\\
 & = & e^{T}-e^{0}\\
 & = & e^{T}-1.\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

 For 
\begin_inset Formula $T\rightarrow\infty$
\end_inset

 the integral diverges, which means that the area under 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x)=e^{x}$
\end_inset

 is not finite.
\end_layout

