\begin_inset LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:norm11"

\end_inset

), (
\begin_inset LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:norm2"

\end_inset

) and (
\begin_inset LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:norm3"

\end_inset

).
 Infact, those properties are usually used to define a norm on a vector
 space.
 Since there are several possible norms on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

